body:
@joel-shor I'm trying out TFGAN in eager execution mode. Unfortunately, [the TFGAN MNIST tutorial](https://github.com/tensorflow/models/blob/master/research/gan/tutorial.ipynb) is not compatible because `download_and_convert_mnist.py` from `models/research/slim` [uses placeholders](https://github.com/tensorflow/models/blob/a3669a934961f71894f959f2765182d6d5062931/research/slim/datasets/download_and_convert_mnist.py#L117).

The Eager MNIST example [uses the Dataset API](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/d87a9fbbc5f49ec5ae8eb52c62628f0b1a0bf67f/tensorflow/contrib/eager/python/examples/mnist/mnist.py#L135).

Is it possible to use the Dataset API with TFGAN at this moment? If so, is there an example of this? Thanks!
